Quiz 2

Select 10 out of 14

20 minutes









CSS Framework: 

Please use either Bootstrap 4 or W3.css to answer following questions.





Example question: Create a small button

Bootstrap 4 answer: <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm">Small</button>

W3.CSS answer: <button class="w3-button w3-small">Small</button>





Button:





1. Create a black/dark button.

Bootstrap 4 answer:<button type="button" class="btn btn-dark">Dark</button>


2. Create a white button with red border

Bootstrap 4 answer:<button type="button" class="btn btn-danger">Danger</button>


3. Create a disabled red button.


Bootstrap 4 answer:<button type="button" class="btn btn-danger disabled">Disabled Danger</button>



Form:





1. Create a form with an email input and a password input

Bootstrap 4 answer:<form>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="exampleInputEmail1">Email address</label>
    <input type="email" class="form-control" id="exampleInputEmail1" aria-describedby="emailHelp" placeholder="Enter email">
    <small id="emailHelp" class="form-text text-muted">We'll never share your email with anyone else.</small>
  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="exampleInputPassword1">Password</label>
    <input type="password" class="form-control" id="exampleInputPassword1" placeholder="Password">
  </div>
</form>


2. Create an inline form with one text input

Bootstrap 4 answer:<div class="form-group">
  <label for="usr">Input:</label>
  <input type="text" class="form-control" id="usr">
</div>

3. Create a dropdown

Bootstrap 4 answer:
<div class="dropdown">
  <button class="btn btn-primary dropdown-toggle" type="button" data-toggle="dropdown">Dropdown Example
  <span class="caret"></span></button>
  <ul class="dropdown-menu">
    <li><a href="#">Abc</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">Def</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">Ghi</a></li>
  </ul>
</div>





Grid:





1. Create three equal-width columns 

Bootstrap 4 answer:
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-4">.col-sm-4</div>
  <div class="col-sm-4">.col-sm-4</div>
  <div class="col-sm-4">.col-sm-4</div>
</div>


2. Create two columns of unequal width (25%/75%) 

          



Bootstrap 4 answer:
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-3">.col-sm-3</div>
  <div class="col-sm-9">.col-sm-9</div>
</div>





















ANGULAR:

1. Explain what is controller in MVC?
The ASP.NET MVC framework maps URLs to classes that are referred to as controllers. Controllers process incoming requests, handle user input and interactions, and execute appropriate application logic. A controller class typically calls a separate view component to generate the HTML markup for the request.
 


2. What directive is used to initialize an angular app?
   ng-app 


3. Can an HTML page have multiple “ng-app” directive for bootstrapping multiple AngularJS application?
The answer is NO. The ng-app directive is used to auto-bootstrap an AngularJS application. And according to documentation, only one AngularJS application can be auto-bootstrapped per HTML document.


4. What does the The ng-bind directive used for binding?
The ng-bind directive tells AngularJS to replace the content of an HTML element with the value of a given variable, or expression.
If the value of the given variable, or expression, changes, the content of the specified HTML element will be changed as well.



5. What is $scope?
It is the binding part between the HTML (view) and the JavaScript (controller).When we make a controller in AngularJS, we pass the $scope object as an argument.



6. Which module is required for routing?
the ngRoute module

